      • Serialization Methods

        • readObject

          protected void readObject(java.io.ObjectInputStream ois)
                   throws java.io.IOException,
                          java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
          This method creates a "fields" parameter which stores all the objects read from the input file. Each of the objects or fields are read and assigned to the respective fields in the GameItem class.
          Throws:
          java.io.IOException - if file cannot be read
          java.lang.ClassNotFoundException - if class cannot be found

        • writeObject

          protected void writeObject(java.io.ObjectOutputStream oos)
                    throws java.io.IOException
          This method also creates a parameter "fields" which is set equal to the collection of fields of the current instance of the GameItem objects.
          Throws:
          java.io.IOException - if file cannot be written to
